  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then cut into strips</p><p>Add the <strong>tofu strips</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>marinated tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-soy-broccoli-stir-fry/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>cornflour </strong>to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then add the <strong>marinated tofu </strong>and mix it all together<strong> </strong>until all the tofu is coated<strong> </strong>– this is your<strong> coated tofu</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated tofu</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp, then transfer to a plate lined with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper and reserve the pan – this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-soy-broccoli-stir-fry/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tofu is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> broccoli</strong> into small florets and cut the stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-soy-broccoli-stir-fry/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>broccoli florets </strong>and <strong>stems </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly charred</p><p>Once slightly charred, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-soy-broccoli-stir-fry/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>medium egg noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir for 10 secs to separate the noodles</p><p>Set aside to soak for 5-6 min</p><p>Drain the <strong>soaked noodles </strong>(reserve a little noodle water)</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-soy-broccoli-stir-fry/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic has softened, reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>to the pan</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining cornflour</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook, covered, for 5-6 min or until the <strong>broccoli</strong> is tender with a slight bite and the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-soy-broccoli-stir-fry/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the broccoli is cooking, slice the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</strong> </span>finely</p><p>Once the broccoli is tender, add the <strong>drained noodles</strong> to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min further or until the noodles are coated in sauce – this is your <strong>soy broccoli stir-fry</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of noodle water to the pan if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-tofu-with-soy-broccoli-stir-fry/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>soy broccoli stir-fry</strong> in bowls with the <strong>crispy tofu</strong> on top</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
